The paper proposes a new approach to constructing CNNs using harmonic blocks that learn optimal combinations of spectral filters. This approach is validated through classification tasks on small NORB, CIFAR10 and CIFAR100 datasets. Given this focus on CNNs and image classification, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
